{
  "stem": "20711.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he took us to Budapest into a family whose name was Kolonics-- Sandor and Teresa, also childless couple, who also were very sympathetic to the children who had to-- who was deported or who stayed in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were willing to do any kind of help they could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know how my mother got that contact, because I never heard about that family before.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were willing to take me in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I stayed with them just for a short while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The problem was Budapest started to be very dangerous as far as the bombing concern.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this Kolonics family lived right next to the railroad station, the big international railroad station, which got bombed practically weekly.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And sooner or later the house could have been bombed too.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was really petrified during the bombing-- the experience to be down in a basement with all of those strange people screaming and crying and carrying on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I really had not-- have my family to comfort me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And no matter how nice that family was toward me, it was still, I felt, very lonesome.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My mother didn't stay with me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She practically dropped me off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And from that point on, I realized my mother became like a courier, a courier between me, my father, and brother, between home, to make sure the house is safe and OK.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She was able to do all the traveling because she received an identification, which showed she's Catholic, both of her parents being Catholic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Just because she had a Jewish husband, it did not make her a Jewish woman.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So she was free to go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But her children were not.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So she used her freedom, and she was constantly on the road.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
